{"title_page": "List of Legends of Tomorrow characters", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Legends of Tomorrow'' characters}}\n''[[Legends of Tomorrow]]'' is an [[United States|American]] television series, developed by [[Greg Berlanti]], [[Marc Guggenheim]], [[Phil Klemmer]], and [[Andrew Kreisberg]], based on several characters from [[DC Comics]]. The series premiered in the United States on January 21, 2016, for [[The CW]] television network, and it finished its first season on May 19, 2016. The second season premiered in October 2016 and ended in April 2017. The third season premiered in October 2017 and concluded in April 2018, while the fourth season premiered in October 2018 and wrapped up in April 2019.\n\n''Legends of Tomorrow'' follows Time Master [[Rip Hunter (Arrowverse)|Rip Hunter]] ([[Arthur Darvill]]) whose mission is to stop [[Vandal Savage (Arrowverse)|Vandal Savage]] ([[Casper Crump]]) from killing his wife and child, and destroying the world. The team members (The Legends) who join Rip in the first season are: [[Martin Stein (Arrowverse)|Martin Stein]] ([[Victor Garber]]); [[Ray Palmer (Arrowverse)|Ray Palmer / The Atom]] ([[Brandon Routh]]); [[Sara Lance|Sara Lance / White Canary]] ([[Caity Lotz]]); [[Jefferson Jackson (Arrowverse)|Jefferson Jackson]] ([[Franz Drameh]]); [[Kendra Saunders (Arrowverse)|Kendra Saunders / Hawkgirl]] ([[Ciara Ren\u00e9e]]); [[Carter Hall (Arrowverse)|Carter Hall / Hawkman]] ([[Falk Hentschel]]); [[Mick Rory (Arrowverse)|Mick Rory / Heat Wave]] ([[Dominic Purcell]]); and [[Leonard Snart (Arrowverse)|Leonard Snart / Captain Cold]] ([[Wentworth Miller]]). [[Amy Pemberton (actress)|Amy Pemberton]] voices the [[artificial intelligence|A. I.]] [[Gideon (Legends of Tomorrow)|Gideon]]. At the end of the season, Snart sacrifices himself to save the Legends and Kendra and Carter depart following Savage's defeat. The second season focuses on the remaining Legends fixing points in time that have been changed, called \"aberrations\"; they are joined by historian [[Nate Heywood (Arrowverse)|Nate Heywood / Steel]] ([[Nick Zano]]) and [[Justice Society of America]] member [[Amaya Jiwe|Amaya Jiwe / Vixen]] ([[Maisie Richardson-Sellers]]), and are pitted against the [[Legion of Doom (Arrowverse)|Legion of Doom]], composed of [[Eobard Thawne (Arrowverse)|Eobard Thawne / Reverse-Flash]] ([[Matt Letscher]]), [[Damien Darhk (Arrowverse)|Damien Darhk]] ([[Neal McDonough]]), [[Malcolm Merlyn (Arrowverse)|Malcolm Merlyn]] ([[John Barrowman]]) and a time-displaced Snart. At the end of the season, Rip departs following the Legion's defeat.\n\nThe third season focuses on the Legends repairing anachronisms they have caused through time during their final battle with the Legion of Doom. In addition, they deal with Rip Hunter's Time Bureau, and stalked by a demonic entity, [[Mallus (Arrowverse)|Mallus]], whose disciple, [[Nora Darhk|Nora]] ([[Courtney Ford]]), has resurrected Damien Darhk, her father, and Amaya's future granddaughter [[Kuasa]]. The team is joined by computer hacker [[Zari Tomaz]] ([[Tala Ashe]]) and speedster [[Wally West (Arrowverse)|Wally West / Kid Flash]] ([[Keiynan Lonsdale]]) with Time Bureau agents [[Ava Sharpe]] ([[Jes Macallan]]) and [[Gary Green (Legends of Tomorrow)|Gary Green]] (Adam Tsekhman) becoming close associates. During the season, Martin dies during the Earth-X invasion and Jefferson departs following Martin's death. At the end of the season, Rip dies fighting Mallus and Amaya departs following the demon's defeat. The fourth season focuses on the Legends dealing with the ''fugitives'' \u2013 a group of  monsters of mythic origins that were released when they freed Mallus in order to defeat him being scattered throughout time. The team is joined by Occult detective [[John Constantine (Arrowverse)|John Constantine]] ([[Matt Ryan (actor)|Matt Ryan]]), shape-shifter fugitive [[Charlie (Arrowverse)|Charlie]] (Maisie Richardson-Sellers) and [[Mona Wu]] ([[Ramona Young]]), who can turn into a magical [[Kaupe]] creature. Before the season, Wally has departed to focus on himself, while Nate departs to work for the Time Bureau before eventually returning.\n\nThe following is a list of characters that have appeared on the television series. Many are named for, or are based on DC Comics characters.\n\n==Overview==\n: <small>{{Color box|#bfd|border=darkgray}} = [[Ensemble cast|Main cast]] (credited) </small>\n: <small>{{Color box|#ffdddd|border=darkgray}} = [[Recurring character|Recurring cast]] (4+)</small>\n: <small>{{Color box|#ADD8E6|border=darkgray}} = [[Guest appearance|Guest cast]] (1-3)</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Character\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Portrayed by\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | First appearance\n! colspan=\"6\" scope=\"col\" | Seasons\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9%;\" | [[Legends of Tomorrow (season 1)|1]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9%;\" | [[Legends of Tomorrow (season 2)|2]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9%;\" | [[Legends of Tomorrow (season 3)|3]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9%;\" | [[Legends of Tomorrow (season 4)|4]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9%;\" | [[Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)|5]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"8\" style=\"background-color:#ccccff;\" | Main characters\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Martin Stein (Arrowverse)|Martin Stein / Firestorm]]\n| [[Victor Garber]]\n| rowspan=\"10\" | \"[[Pilot, Part 1]]\"\n| colspan=\"3\" {{CMain}}{{efn|Garber is credited through \"[[Crisis on Earth-X, Part 4]]\".}}\n! colspan=\"2\" {{CNone}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ray Palmer (Arrowverse)|Ray Palmer / Atom]]\n| [[Brandon Routh]]\n| colspan=\"5\" {{CMain|Main}}{{efn|Routh is credited through \"[[Romeo v Juliet: Dawn of Justness]]\".}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Rip Hunter (Arrowverse)|Rip Hunter]]\n| [[Arthur Darvill]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cMain|Main}}\